ales\">leahb@strawdog.org</a></p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(65,80,1,'Group Sales','2019-07-24 01:39:26','2019-07-24 01:39:26','e780c504-d83d-416c-9bc9-286a40c5dbae',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(67,82,1,'Join the Board','2019-07-24 01:39:46','2019-08-02 00:52:38','031a0afd-75f0-424a-8952-cc794406f413',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<h2>STRAWDOG THEATRE IS SEEKING NEW BOARD MEMBERS!</h2>\n<h3>What does the Board of Directors do?</h3>\n<p>Strawdog’s volunteer Board Members make up the governing body of the organization. They support our mission and artistic programming by participating in board and committee meetings, introducing Strawdog to new communities, attending performances and events, and championing our values of Challenge, Community, Ensemble and Genuine Connection.</p>\n<h3>Who can join the Board?</h3>\n<p>Strawdog is looking for individuals who are interested in supporting the performing arts. Whether you are an artist, doctor, lawyer, accountant, business owner, retired, or just looking for an organization to call home—we’d love to meet you!</p>\n<h3>How can I learn more?</h3>\n<p>Email Jennifer Nelson, Strawdog Board President, <a href=\"mailto:JenniferNelson@strawdog.org?subject=Join%20The%20Board\">JenniferNelson@strawdog.org</a> to set time for a short call or cup of coffee.</p>\n<h3>How do I join?</h3>\n<p>Meet one-on-one with at least one active board member, attend two board meetings as an observer to learn first-hand how the board operates, and accept formal invitation to join after the board votes to invite you</p>\n<p>Strawdog Theatre Company is an equal opportunity employer and considers