 IL 60613</p>\n<p><strong>Monthly or Quarterly</strong> Select \"Recurring gift\" when making a donation online and choose the amount you\'d like to give monthly or quarterly, and we\'ll automatically bill your debit or credit card. Being able to count on regular income means the world to scrappy organizations like Strawdog!</p>\n<p><strong>Matching Gifts</strong> Many employers offer a matching gift program that allows you to increase your giving to your favorite organization. This can double or even triple your gift to Strawdog, giving you the increased benefits and visibility that comes with your new level of giving. Inquire with your company\'s human resources department to see if your gift to Strawdog qualifies for a matching gift.</p>\n<p><strong>Planned Giving</strong> Share your passion for the theater by making a gift to Strawdog in your will or estate plans. Your gift can provide financial security to Strawdog while offering you and your estate significant tax and other financial benefits.</p>\n<p><strong>In-Kind Support</strong> Supporters can also donate their time, goods, or services in-kind. Donate food or drink to our next event, or office furniture, or doors...almost anything! Contact Development Associate at <a href=\"mailto:virginia@strawdog.org?subject=In-Kind%25Support\">jhr@strawdog.org</a> for more information.<strong><br /></strong></p><p><strong>Donor Levels and Benefits</strong><br />To thank you for your generosity, Strawdog is pleased to offer donors a number of exciting benefits. If you have questions about your membership level or benefits, please contact Individual Giving Manager Virginia Head by emailing <a href=\"mailto:virginia@strawdog.org?subject=Individual%20Giving%20Question\">virginia@strawdog.org.</a></p>\n<h4>FRIENDS OF STRAWDOG</h4>\n<h5>$125-$249 - Sponsor</h5>\n<ul><li>Recognition in our performance programs and online for one year!</li><li>Early access to tickets for extension performances and special events</li></ul><h5>$250-$499 - Contributor</h5>\n<p>All of the above, plus:</p>\n<ul><li>Invitation to a technical rehearsal</li><li>Commemorative Poster from Recent Show, signed by the cast</li></ul><h5>$500-$999 - Sustainer</h5>\n<p>All of the above, plus:</p>\n<ul><li>Prominent recognition in the performance program and on our website for one year</li><li>Invitation to a Backstage Tour led by an Ensemble member</li></ul><h5>$1,000-$2,499 - Director</h5>\n<p>All of the above, plus:</p>\n<ul><li>Recognition on the Wall of Thanks in our new lobby!</li></ul><h4>PRODUCERS CIRCLE</h4>\n<h5>$2,500-$4,999 - Associate Producer</h5>\n<p>All of the above, plus:</p>\n<ul><li>Listing as \"Associate Producer\" for your chosen production</li><li>Year-long recognition as \"Associate Producer\" in performance programs, on the website, and on the Wall of Thanks in our new lobby</li><li>Two complimentary tickets to Board Night performance and reception of your chosen production</li></ul><h5>$5000-$9,999 - Producer</h5>\n<p>All of the above, plus:</p>\n<ul><li>Recognition as \"Producer\" for your chosen production</li><li>Year-long recognition as \"Producer\" in performance programs and on the website</li><li>Invitation to the first rehearsal and read-through of your chosen production</li><li>Four complimentary tickets to Board Night performance and reception of your chosen production</li></ul><h5>$10,000+ - Executive Producer</h5>\n<p>All of the above, plus:</p>\n<ul><li>Recognition as \"Executive Producer\" for your chosen production</li><li>Year-long recognition as \"Executive Producer\" in performance programs and on the website</li><li>Six complimentary tickets to Board Night performance and reception of your chosen production</li><li>A Personalized behind-the-scenes experience. Let us work with you to create a benefits package that fits your interests!</li></ul>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(121,142,1,'Join the Board','2019-07-25 00:22:38','2019-07-25 00:22:38','6bc27a15-b27f-4071-80e0-1f727455489d',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p><strong>STRAWDOG THEATRE IS SEEKING NEW BOARD MEMBERS!</strong><br /></p>\n<p>What does the Board of Directors do?</p>\n\n<p>Strawdog’s volunteer Board Members make up the governing body of the organization. They support our mission and artistic programming by participating in board and committee meetings, introducing Strawdog to new communities, attending performances and events, and championing our values of Challenge, Community, Ensemble and Genuine Connection.</p>\n\n\n<p>Who can join the Board?</p>\n\n\n<p>Strawdog is looking for individuals who are interested in supporting the performing arts. Whether you are an artist, doctor, lawyer, accountant, business owner, retired, or just looking for an organization to call home – we’d love to meet you!</p>\n\n\n<p>How can I learn more?</p>\n\n\n<p>Email Jennifer Nelson, Strawdog Board President, JenniferNelson@strawdog.org to set time for a short call or cup of coffee.</p>\n\n\n<p>How do I join?</p>\n\n\n<p>Meet one-on-one with at least one active board member, Attend two board meetings as an observer to learn first-hand how the board operates, Accept formal invitation to join, after the board votes to invite you</p>\n\n\n<p>Strawdog Theatre Company is an equal opportunity employer and considers applicants for all positions without regard to race, color, religion, creed, gender, national origin, age, disability, marital or veteran status, sexual orientation, or any other legally protected status.</p>\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(122,143,1,'Audition','2019-07-25 00:24:40','2019-07-25 00:24:40','610cfacf-c434-4bd9-9a3f-f65ef00e9034',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p><strong>Where to send headshots and resumes</strong><br />Strawdog holds auditions per production and accepts headshots and resumes throughout the year. It is very important that we have current contact information. Please notify us any time you change your telephone number or union status. Actors should send headshots and/or resumes to the attention of:</p>\n<p>Casting Director<br />Strawdog Theatre Company<br />1802 W Berenice Ave<br />Chicago, IL 60613</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(123,144,1,'Open Positions','2019-07-25 00:27:40','2019-07-25 00:27:40','60a6f9b1-77e6-40ef-911b-73bed71bdba1',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Content TK</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(124,145,1,'Contact Us','2019-07-25 00:30:18','2019-07-25 01:00:22','d50d8057-5c25-4455-923c-fb98c014c07e',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<h4>ADDRESS</h4>\n<p><strong>Strawdog Theatre Company</strong><br />1802 W Berenice Ave<br />Chicago IL 60613</p>\n<h4>TELEPHONE</h4>\n<p><a href=\"tel:7736441380\">773.644.1380</a></p>\n<h4>EMAIL</h4>\n<figure><a href=\"mailto:boxoffice@strawdog.org?subject=Strawdog%20Theatre%20Company%20-%20Contact\"><img src=\"http://strawdog.org/images/envelope_new.gif\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" /><strong>boxoffice@strawdog.org</strong></a></figure><h4>STAFF</h4>\n<figure><a href=\"mailto:ledahoffmann@strawdog.org?subject=Strawdog%20Theatre%20Company%20-%20Artistic%20Director\"><img src=\"http://strawdog.org/images/envelope_new.gif\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" /> Artistic Director</a></figure><p>Leda Hoffmann</p>\n<figure><a href=\"mailto:charlotte@strawdog.org?subject=Strawdog%20Theatre%20Company%20-%20Managing%20Director\"><img src=\"http://strawdog.org/images/envelope_new.gif\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" /> Managing Director</a></figure><p>Charlotte Thomas</p>\n<figure><a href=\"mailto:cheath@strawdog.org?subject=Strawdog%20Theatre%20Company%20-%20Literary%20Manager\"><img src=\"http://strawdog.org/images/envelope_new.gif\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" /> Literary Manager</a></figure><p>Cara Beth Heath</p>\n<figure><a href=\"mailto:kamille@strawdog.org?subject=Strawdog%20Theatre%20Company%20-%20Diversity%20Committee%20Chair\"><img src=\"http://strawdog.org/images/envelope_new.gif\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" /> Diversity Committee Chair</a></figure><p>Kamille Dawkins</p>\n<figure><a href=\"mailto:kanome@strawdog.org?subject=Strawdog%20Theatre%20Company%20-%20Casting%20Director\"><img src=\"http://strawdog.org/images/envelope_new.gif\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" /> Casting Director</a></figure>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(131,152,1,'Plan Your Visit','2019-07-25 00:36:09','2019-07-25 01:00:31','e875f401-da29-4e2e-9be1-e6267c9882b0',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p><strong>Public Transit</strong>: take the <strong>brown line</strong> to the Irving Park Station and exit at the south end of the platform. This will put you on the south side of Irving Park Ave. Go east on Irving Park just ½ block and turn right on Ravenswood (staying on the west side of the Metra tracks) and walk south to Berenice. Our theatre will be on your right.</p>\n<p><strong>By Car</strong>: Take <strong>Lakeshore Drive</strong> and exit on Irving Park Ave. Continue west to turn left on Ravenswood Avenue (just west of the Metra tracks). Turn right on Berenice Avenue. Our theatre will be on your right. OR take <strong>I-94</strong> and exit on Irving Park Ave. Go east on Irving Park, then turn right on Ravenswood Avenue.</p>\n<h4>PARKING</h4>\n<p>Parking is available in the lot to the west of the theatre building, against the wall of the theatre. The parking lot is accessible via the alley, which you can access via Byron or Ravenswood. You cannot access the parking lot from Berenice Ave. There is non-permitted street parking on Ravenswood and Berenice Ave. <strong>Do not park in any spots labeled BLACK BEAR ACADEMY—they will tow!</strong></p><h4>EAT &amp; DRINK IN NORTH CENTER</h4>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.begylebrewing.com/home/\">Begyle Brewery</a><br />800 W Cuyler Ave | (773) 661-6963<br />Straightforward microbrewery &amp; retailer teaming its craft beers with tours &amp; more. Plus they\'re Strawdog\'s beer sponsor!<br /></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.brownstonetavern.com/\">Brownstone Tavern</a><br />3937 N Lincoln Ave | (773) 528-3700<br />Spacious neighborhood sports bar featuring outdoor seating &amp; a menu of upscale pub grub.<br /></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://bigbrickschicago.com/\">Big Bricks</a><br />3832 N Lincoln Ave | (773) 525-5022 <br />Low-key pizzeria serving Chicago staples of beer, thin-crust pizza &amp; BBQ pork with an upscale twist.<br /></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://eatorangegarden.com/zgrid/themes/10592/intro/index.jsp\">Orange Garden</a><br />1942 W Irving Park Rd | (773) 525-7479<br />Chinese mainstay for old-school Cantonese cooking in simple rooms with art &amp; artifacts since 1932.<strong><br /></strong></p>\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(137,158,1,'Performance Space and Rentals','2019-07-25 00:38:26','2019-07-25 00:38:26','30d27f6c-250c-42d1-b9c8-db78723d9f5a',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<h2>Location</h2>\n<p>Strawdog\'s 30th season continues in our new home at <strong>1802 West Berenice Avenue</strong>, in Chicago\'s North Center neighborhood.<br /></p>\n\n<h2>Rent Our Space</h2>\n<p>Strawdog\'s beautiful 80 seat black box theatre located at 1802 W Berenice Ave is available to rent! We aim to fill it day and night with Chicago theatre artists who want to help give life to this new basecamp for our work and our community. It\'s a flexible, easily configurable space perfect for performances, staged readings, auditions, rehearsals and other events. Our scene shop is fully equipped with a variety of tools and building space.</p>\n<p>Rental fees for performances, late nights, rehearsals, shop space, and special events vary. Email <a href=\"mailto:rentals@strawdog.org\">rentals@strawdog.org </a>with questions about the space, rates, and availability.</p>\n<h2>Rent Our Stuff</h2>\n<p>Strawdog has lighting and sound equipment, furniture, instruments, and more available to rent.</p>\n<p>Email <a href=\"mailto:rentals@strawdog.org\">rentals@strawdog.org </a>for rates and availability.</p>\n<p>Examples of available items include:</p>\n<ul><li>10 x Black highboy tables</li><li>20 x Black high Stools</li><li>1 x ETC Ion 2000, compatible with ETC Nomad</li><li>10 x ColorBlast TRX (RGBAW) w/ Power Supply</li><li>6 x Strip Lights</li><li>1 x Panasonic DZ6700U 6000 Lumen WUXGA (1920x1200) DLP projector</li><li>1 x Epson EX-31 2500 Lumen SVGA (800x600) LCD projector</li><li>1 x Piano</li><li>Much, much more. We have a lot of stuff.</li></ul>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(138,159,1,'Our Supporters','2019-07-25 00:40:06','2019-07-25 01:00:27','31db442d-0ff9-421d-8b0d-af7a6471b1f3',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p><strong>Thank you!</strong><br />Strawdog is pleased to be able to recognize the generous contributions of the following individuals, foundations, a