p dynamics.<br /><br /><strong>Providing Support:</strong> We acknowledge and welcome the potential presence of survivors in the room and recognize that aspects of the workshop may be challenging and sensitive by nature. Support is provided throughout the workshop to anyone, as needed, by a Licensed Clinical Professional Counselor.<br /><br />This course requires no martial arts training, nor extreme physical aptitudes. All skill levels are welcome and encouraged. <br /><br /><a href=\"https://www.chicagomindandbody.com/about-the-founder/\"><strong>Sarah Farris</strong></a> (she/her/hers) works as a therapist and part-time nutrition counselor. She curates healthy lifestyle practices for her clients. She has also expanded a new business \"Chicago Mind &amp; Body\"<br /><br /><a><strong>Cassidy Hill</strong></a> (she/her/hers) As a Certified Personal Trainer with an affinity for martial arts, Cassidy Hill loves helping people feel strong, confident, and capable. Her self defense background involves a hefty combination of Tae Kwon Do, Kung Fu, Hapkido, and Aikido. She is thrilled to be working with By Womxn For Womxn, which offers both a safe space, and a unique environment where we get to lift each other up, showing each other how powerful we can truly be. <br /><br /><a href=\"http://strawdog.org/index.php?shot=mpetro_large.jpg&amp;section=company&amp;person=michaelapetro\"><strong>Michaela Petro</strong></a> (she/her/hers) is an actor and certified trainer of self-defense &amp; rape prevention with the American Women\'s Self-Defense Association (AWSDA). As an ensemble member of Strawdog Theatre Company, one of her core beliefs is serving her community and does so by sharing empowerment skills.</p>',NULL,'https://red.vendini.com/ticket-software.html?t=tix&e=22a03b7c38d433a51f2ac69c3fd10a2a','<p>A new way, led by womxn: learn a three-tiered approach to self-defense for all skill levels.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2019-07-29 