sely with the audience through new and familiar stories, is and will be amazing. Off stage, you may find him baking, daydreaming, and just generally trying to remain curious.<br /></p>',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(446,649,1,'Hero image michaelapetro','2019-07-30 00:33:39','2019-08-04 03:39:30','dc154578-451f-498d-bbb0-306c2120c9bb',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(447,650,1,'Michaela Petro','2019-07-30 00:33:42','2019-07-30 00:33:42','cc6a9fdb-adce-45ae-8e84-525d89f540b3',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>\"Think of me what you will, I\'ve got a little space to fill.\"<br /><br />Hailing from the East Coast, and loving story-telling, Michaela moved to Chicago to study fiction writing at Columbia College. However, after one look at the Getz\'s stage housing nothing but a ghost light, she changed her major and began to pursue theater.<br /><br />After completion of the theater program in 2004 she began work with The Lakeside Shakespeare Theatre for 6 seasons. Her time spent with LST allowed her to run the gamut from Juliet in <em>Romeo and Juliet</em>, to The Boy in <em>Henry V</em>.<br /><br />Within the city\'s limits she has been seen performing with Cole Theatre, Lifeline Theatre, Interrobang, WildClaw Theatre (with which she is a company member/ resident berserker), Mary-Arrchie at Angel Island, The Journeymen, City Lit and many others. However, she began working with Strawdog on <em>WRLS 4</em>in 2005 and has been around ever since. <br /><br />Allowed to reestablish herself as a singer, and reinvent herself time and time again, are just two of the reasons she esteems herself lucky to be a part of this talented family of people.<br /><br />She loves tea, baking, t-shirts and rock-n-roll. Though word on the street is she\'s graceless, she\'ll never stop striving. Besides, she heals miraculously quickly.<br /><br />\"Follow the fear.\"</p>',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(448,651,1,'Hero image daniellapereira','2019-07-30 00:34:09','2019-08-04 03:39:32','3a0f2962-ec00-45a6-bcb8-4b159a1ba0b9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(449,652,1,'Daniella Pereira','2019-07-30 00:34:12','2019-07-30 00:34:12','a5b733b8-1c2a-46fe-985b-9f29ba4c65b8',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Originally from Miami, Florida, this little Latina left everything she knew to pursue her dreams in the frigid Windy City. She received a bachelor in fine arts at the Chicago College of Performing Arts. Although she has still not become accustomed to the weather...even after being here for 5 years, she is truly in awe of the city and its magic. She is a proud first generation Colombian American.<br /><br />Since graduating, Daniella has appeared in <em>Letters Home</em> (Griffin Theatre Company), <em>The Taming of the Shrew</em> (Oak Park Festival Theatre), <em>Here Lies the water/Here stands the man</em> (Nadja Leonard-Hopper and Genevieve Fowler), <em>Cymbeline</em> (Strawdog Theatre Company), and <em>Women Laughing Alone with Salad</em>beginning March 2018 (Theatre Wit). Daniella is honored and incredibly thankful to be joining Strawdog\'s ensemble, and cannot wait to work with such determined and inspiring individuals.<br /><br />She is represented by Gray Talent Group.<br /><br />Daniella loves the sun, the water, the sand between her toes, and pretty much everything that has to do with outer space.</p>',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(450,653,1,'Hero image janiceoneill','2019-07-30 00:34:39','2019-08-04 03:39:32','acd85765-e081-4c81-abfb-9d9e27d22bb7',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(451,654,1,'Janice O’Neill','2019-07-30 00:34:41','2019-07-30 00:34:41','9ce95e58-43bf-462f-bde6-ef061bcee6b5',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Janice has appeared in Strawdog productions of <em>Conversations on a Homecoming</em> as Missus, directed by Jonathan Berry, and in <em>The Petrified Forest</em> as Mrs. Chisholm, directed by Shade Murray. Other Chicago theatre roles include: Carol in <em>A Permanent Image</em>with LiveWire, Mme. de Volanges in <em>Les Liaisons Dangereuses</em> at Remy Bumppo, <em>The Sugar Syndrome</em> at Chicago Dramatists, Sister Margurite in <em>Mariette in Ecstasy</em> (Non-Equity Jeff nomination, Best Ensemble), Honor in <em>Voysey Inheritance</em> with Remy Bummpo, Dolores (u/s) in <em>Mary</em> at The Goodman, Juror #8 in <em>Twelve Angry Jurors</em> at Oil Lamp Theatre, Anna in <em>Nocturne</em> at EP Theatre, <em>Symmetry</em> (replacement) at Victory Gardens and Agnes (replacement) in <em>A Delicate Balance.</em> Film Credits include: Jackie Costa in <em>Prayers for Bobby,</em> Mother in <em>Mulligan,</em> Catherine in <em>Carpet Kingdom</em> and Myra in <em>Moontrap</em>. Represented by Stewart Talent Chicago for over 20 years, Janice has appeared in hundreds of commercials and industrial films.<br /></p>',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(452,655,1,'Hero image katmcdonnell','2019-07-30 00:35:03','2019-08-04 03:39:33','78854b24-3ffe-4894-acee-4f232adad6a3',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(453,656,1,'Kat McDonnell','2019-07-30 00:35:05','2019-07-30 00:35:05','bba468b3-e37d-4b40-95d7-2eb104a7410b',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Chicago credits include: <em>Well</em> at Next Theatre; <em>Scenes from the Big Picture</em> at Seanachai Theatre; <em>Pursued by Happiness</em> at Steppenwolf Theatre/First Look; <em>Dolly West\'s Kitchen</em> at TimeLine Theatre; <em>The Sparrow</em> (Jeff Award - Ensemble) and <em>Valentine Victorious</em> at The House Theatre of Chicago. Recent Strawdog credits include: <em>Old Town</em> (After Dark Award - Outstanding Performance in a Musical), <em>Marathon \'33</em> (Jeff Award - Best Ensemble) and <em>Three Sisters</em> (Jeff Nomination - Actress in a Principal Role). Kat is a proud company member of Strawdog and The House Theatre of Chicago.<br /></p>',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(454,657,1,'Hero image beccalevy','2019-07-30 00:35:29','2019-08-04 03:39:31','816e7814-4938-4625-b876-692a5ef3620c',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(455,658,1,'Becca Levy','2019-07-30 00:35:33','2019-07-30 00:35:33','4a7d23ec-4522-4a87-a6e8-1ee01dedf397',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Becca Levy is delighted to join Strawdog\'s ensemble with the class of 2018! The first show she stage managed with Strawdog, <em>D.O.A.,</em> was the final show in Hugen Hall, Strawdog\'s old home on Broadway. She knew immediately that Strawdog would be an artistic home for her in Chicago. She continued to work with Strawdog through a major transition, stage managing <em>Distance</em>and <em>Cymbeline</em> in Season 29, while we were in between spaces, before being asked to join the staff as Production Manager for Season 30. She has been honored and excited to help Strawdog grow as we settle into our new home on Berenice.<br /><br />Becca is a freelance stage manager, production manager, and teaching artist and has worked with various fantastic Chicago theatre companies including Chicago Shakespeare Theater, Emerald City Theatre, Jackalope Theatre Company, Red Theater, Pinebox Theatre Company, and she was the Company Stage Manager for the winter 2017 run of <em>Potted Potter</em> with Starvox Touring and Seabright Productions at Broadway in Chicago\'s Broadway Playhouse. She is also the PSM of the Opera Program at Northeastern Illinois University. Outside of Chicago, Becca has worked on stage management teams at Networks Touring Presentations and Famers Alley Theatre.<br /><br />\"Find a group of people who challenge and inspire you, spend a lot of time with them, and it will change your life. No one is here today because they did it on their own.\" - Queen of the world, Amy Poehler</p>',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(456,659,1,'Hero image andersonlawfer','2019-07-30 00:35:56','2019-08-04 03:39:31','ea3a8c14-377a-42da-b546-25f51e0d356f',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(457,660,1,'Anderson Lawfer','2019-07-30 00:35:59','2019-07-30 00:35:59','a0e87dda-4f93-4e48-9b1c-759bdb7641fc',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Anderson is a host, creator, actor, writer, and director.<br /><br />As an actor, he has appeared in numerous productions with Strawdog since joining the company in 2004, as well as The Factory, The House Theatre of Chicago, Chemically Imbalanced, Emerald City, Steep Theatre, and The Alley Theatre in his hometown of Louisville.<br /><br />He is the Artistic Director of Hugen Hall, where he directed and co-adapted to stage the hit production of <em>Fail/Safe</em> and is creator and host of a staple in Strawdog late-night programming, <em>Theatre Wars!</em><br /><br />Most recently, he was featured as the beguiling Daniel in the US premiere of <em>Quiz Show</em> and will be appearing on stage in <em>Once in a Lifetime</em> this spring.</p>',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(458,661,1,'Hero image johnkelly','2019-07-30 00:36:31','2019-08-04 03:39:32','da18d72d-2c7c-4742-a41b-71deeccf936e',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(459,662,1,'John Kelly','2019-07-30 00:36:33','2019-07-30 00:36:33','8fd12c54-9b24-4b99-8693-819297762353',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>John Kelly has been part of the Strawdog ensemble since 2014. His favorite Strawdog projects have been <em>Great Expectations, D.O.A., Charles Ives Take Me Home, 20,000 Leagues Under the Sea</em>and <em>Improbable Frequency</em> (asst. to Jordan Kardasz).<br /><br />John has designed for other companies including The Neofutursts, Lifeline Theatre, Theatre Wit, About Face Theatre, The New Colony, Sideshow Theatre, The Gift Theatre, Step Up Productions and RedTwist.<br /><br />Elsewhere in Chicago he has been the lighting supervisor for Chicago Children\'s Theatre since 2014 and has been a lighting sub at Blue Man Group. He\'s also worked as the tour electrician for Chicago Shakespeare\'s Short Shakespeare and Shakespeare in the Park tour.<br /><br />For more info please visit <a href=\"http://www.johnkellydesigns.com/\">www.johnkellydesigns.com</a></p>',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(460,663,1,'Hero image samhubbard','2019-07-30 00:36:59','2019-08-04 03:39:28','1ba0dc10-12bc-469e-bbe4-11d684d3ee39',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(461,664,1,'Sam Hubbard','2019-07-30 00:37:01','2019-07-30 00:37:01','bda831a6-f898-46a1-a82b-b83464664d03',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Sam Hubbard has appeared in Strawdog\'s <em>Neighborhood 3: Requisition of Doom</em>, <em>The Long Christmas Ride Home</em>, <em>Cymbeline</em>, and <em>Damascus</em>. He\'s directed fights for many many Strawdog productions including <em>Great Expectations</em>, <em>Barbecue</em>, <em>After Miss Julie</em>, <em>Charles Ives Take Me Home</em>, <em>Robin Hood</em>, <em>Quiz Show</em>, and more. Acting credits include <em>The Book of Will</em> (Northlight Theatre), <em>A Loss of Roses, Playboy of the Western World</em> (Raven Theatre), <em>The Diary of Anne Frank</em> (Writers Theatre), <em>Cymbeline</em>, <em>Hamlet</em> (Michigan Shakespeare Festival), productions with The Factory, Oak Park Festival Theatre, Jackalope and understudy roles at Steppenwolf, Chicago Shakespeare Theatre, Writers, and Northlight.<br /><br />Fight Direction credits include productions with Court Theatre, Northlight, Steppenwolf for Young Adults, Timeline, Victory Gardens, Raven, Steep, Jackalope, Teatro Vista, Redtwist, First Floor, The Artistic Home, Haven Theatre and the late Mary-Arrchie.<br />Sam is a graduate of Columbia College Chicago and represented by the fine folks at Grossman &amp; Jack and NV Talent</p>',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(462,665,1,'Hero image shannonhoag','2019-07-30 00:37:27','2019-08-04 03:39:28','ef9ad4d8-9bbb-4145-90bb-1623d3add81e',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(463,666,1,'Shannon Hoag','2019-07-30 00:37:29','2019-07-30 00:37:29','7ff6c1f7-5755-4624-a6a6-6d47886c0507',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Shannon first met the Dogs working on <em>The Green Bird</em>, playing the stony and yet questionably clothed Pompea. While extremely daunting, thrilling, and fun, this initial Strawdog experience secured many things in her life—a deep love for the company, a great respect for Strawdog’s place in Chicago&amp;$8217;s theatrical community, and a wonderful husband. Not bad.<br /><br />Shannon is a graduate of Illinois Wesleyan University (Much love Dr. Ficca), and has also completed studies at The National Theatre Institute at the Eugene O’Neill Theater Center, The Moscow Art Theatre and The London Academy of Theatre. While extremely daunting, thrilling and fun, this global academic odyssey also secured many things in her life—Big love for Mother Russia, a schizophrenic blend of theatrical interests, and a lifelong aversion to beets.<br /><br />Shannon has had the pleasure of working with some great companies including: Visions and Voices (<em>The Devil’s Sonata</em>), Breadline and Clark Island Shakespeare, and has done voice-over work around town. She also serves as Strawdog’s Press Relations Coordinator.<br /><br />Originally from Batavia, IL, a town famous for Fermilab, windmills, and The Becky, Shannon loves her new home in Chicago, her wonderful family and friends and whatever comes next.<br /></p>',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(464,667,1,'A record player and speaker.','2019-07-30 00:37:53','2019-08-08 01:20:50','13dde0a5-ad75-487c-bcf6-fdbe72cfd08a',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(465,668,1,'Heath Hays','2019-07-30 00:37:55','2019-07-30 00:37:55','b266dfdb-5b74-433e-8239-da0940b1037d',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Heath was born and (mostly) raised in the verdant rolling hills of northeast Indiana. By middle school, he had burgeoning career portraying street urchins, in many permutations, at the local high school and community theatres.<br /><br />This all changed in college. Leaving behind the limelight, he took the mantle of designer, and has been such ever since. After moving to Chicago in 2003, he has worked for too many theatre companies, collectives, ensembles, co-ops, and loose knit groups to name. And he had a good time in every show except one. With Strawdog, Heath has designed sound for <em>Improbable Frequency</em>, <em>Big Love</em>, and <em>Conversations on a Homecoming</em>. He has been a supporter of everything else.</p>',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(466,669,1,'Hero image kylehamman','2019-07-30 00:38:20','2019-08-04 03:39:33','d8e2d74e-c187-4049-9447-cb461feb0f46',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(467,670,1,'Kyle Hamman','2019-07-30 00:38:22','2019-07-30 00:38:22','5c9d060e-3031-40de-ad54-fd2226ad08d2',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Kyle Hamman is the owner/operator of KBH Media, a small multi-media production company that specializes in visual storytelling. Hamman has been involved in Chicago theatre as an actor, designer, director and producer for almost 15 years and has been a member of the Strawdog Ensemble since 2000. He has appeared in over twenty Strawdog productions and facilitated numerous others behind the scenes. Hamman is originally from North Little Rock, Arkansas. After graduating from Ouachita Baptist University, Hamman spent a season at Actors Theatre of Louisville as an acting apprentice before relocating to Chicago. Hamman has worked with numerous theatres in Chicago including Mary-Arrchie, CollaborAction, Noble Fool, Northlight, Serendipity, Teatro Vista, Theatre Seven, WildClaw Theatre (Associate Artist), Writers Theatre, and The Factory where he directed Ren Faire! A Fistful of Ducats. Hamman has been nominated for Jeff Citations as a Best Actor, Best Supporting Actor and Best Director. He is married to fellow Strawdog Ensemble member Shannon Hoag.<br /></p>',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(468,671,1,'Hero image carminegrisolia','2019-07-30 00:38:47','2019-08-04 03:39:32','ad44d9c8-7a50-4811-a05f-260fb866453a',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(469,672,1,'Carmine Grisolia','2019-07-30 00:38:50','2019-07-30 00:38:50','f4f2a6f7-372d-404e-b4d9-8c4481f22921',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Carmine Grisolia was last seen here wearing leather pants, screaming into a microphone, and dying in a pool of his own blood during <em>Tooth of Crime</em> -- which incidentally, his grandmother LOVED. Other recent favorite appearances include Puntila in <em>Puntila and His Man Matti,</em> and Mel Vallette in the Strawdog Radio Series. Look for him in the next installment, too. Carm offers his thanks to everyone for coming out to see Strawdog productions, and hopes you enjoyed the fancy new seats.</p>',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(470,673,1,'Hero image sarahgoeden','2019-07-30 00:39:28','2019-08-04 03:39:28','17ad1982-72a8-4846-b3d0-36f21ffd4218',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(471,674,1,'Sarah Goeden','2019-07-30 00:39:30','2019-07-30 00:39:30','f0bfd428-cadb-4dbc-8095-3bb05eab5fca',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Sarah Goeden has appeared in <em>Master and Margarita</em> (Jeff Nomination, Best Ensemble) and in the original and remount of <em>Red Noses</em> (Jeff nomination, Best Ensemble) both here at Strawdog. Her other recent Chicago credits include <em>Mariette in Ecstacy</em> (Jeff nomination, Best Ensemble) and <em>Wuthering Heights</em>, both with Lifeline Theatre; <em>It’s a Wonderful Life</em> with the tour cast of American Theatre Company; <em>I Alone Escaped to Tell Thee of Moby Dick</em> and <em>Cabaret of Desire</em>, both with Blair Thomas and Company; “The Mime Show” in the <em>Picked Up</em> series with The Neofuturists; <em>Dustbowl Gothic</em>, <em>Moby Dick</em>, and <em>Noir</em>, all with The Building Stage; and <em>13 Dead Husbands</em> with Sansculottes Theatre (New City’s Top 5 Female Performances of 2008). Sarah is also a proud company member with Barrel of Monkeys.</p>',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(472,675,1,'Hero image ellygreen','2019-07-30 00:39:39','2019-08-04 03:39:32','ef92abd0-e7f9-4c92-b95b-dbeebe480a23',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(473,676,1,'Elly Green','2019-07-30 00:39:41','2019-07-30 00:39:41','90f6c6cf-32c3-46bc-bac5-99e37ab7a5c7',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Elly is a freelance director, originally from the UK, who has been working in Chicago since 2012. She is directing <em>The Night Season</em>by Rebecca Lenkiewicz in Season 29, and previously worked with Strawdog on <em>After Miss Julie</em> by Patrick Marber (based on the Strindberg).<br /><br />Other directing credits include: <em>The Distance</em> (Haven Theatre), <em>No More Sad Things</em> (Sideshow Theatre), <em>The Woman Before</em> (Trap Door), <em>Rabbit</em> (Stage Left — Jeff Nominated Best Director), <em>Happy</em> (Redtwist), <em>Unwilling and Hostile Instruments</em> (Theatre Seven) and <em>The Tomkat Project</em> (Playground Theatre &amp; NY Fringe). Elly was assistant director on <em>Henry V</em> (Chicago Shakespeare Theatre) and <em>Proof</em> (Court Theatre). She is also an artistic associate with Sideshow Theatre and Stage Left Theatre.<br /><br />Elly originally trained in London on the MFA in Theatre Directing from Birkbeck College. Her UK directing credits include: <em>Our Country\'s Good, My Balloon Beats Your Astronaut, Beyond Therapy, About Tommy, Copenhagen, Skylight, The Beach</em> &amp; <em>The Zoo Story.</em> For more information see <a href=\"http://strawdog.org/www.ellygreendirector.com\">www.ellygreendirector.com</a></p>',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(474,677,1,'Hero image johnferrick','2019-07-30 00:40:03','2019-08-04 03:39:32','517af651-3be9-4128-866c-b6cc773f3415',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(475,678,1,'John Ferrick','2019-07-30 00:40:06','2019-07-30 00:40:06','4ba75c4e-aa5e-4714-8fa1-c9cef46cb0fc',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>An ensemble member since 2001, John joined Strawdog shortly after performing the role of Robert Sideway in <em>Our Country\'s Good</em>. Up next in 2014 he will be finishing off an 11 month run of back to back to back shows with <em>Monstrous Regiment</em> by Terry Prachit adapted by Chris Hainsworth and directed by Kevin Theis at Lifeline Theatre. He has appeared in over a dozen shows at Strawdog, most notably Andre in <em>Three Sisters</em>, Marc Antony in <em>Julius Caesar</em>, Flote in <em>Red Noses</em> and <em>Red Noses Remounted</em>, Nikos in <em>Big Love</em>, Joe and others in <em>Great Expectations</em> , and most recently Aveling in <em>Miss Marx</em>. </p>\n<p>Here at Strawdog, John is an active part of the Literary Committee and gets to read tons of interesting plays and help funnel the best ones to our stages for you to enjoy. Prior to working with Strawdog, he performed with Mike Dailey in About Face Theatre\'s inaugural production of <em>Dream Boy</em> at the old Eclipse Theatre space in Bucktown far far too many years ago. John is also an Artistic Associate at THE DIVISION. He has also worked on multiple productions at Lifeline Theatre, including <em>The Count of Monte Cristo</em>, <em>Watership Down</em>, <em>Treasure Island</em>, <em>The Picture of Dorian Gray</em>, <em>The Mark of Zorro</em>, <em>Talking it Over</em>, and (working with Ned Mochel as director) the critically acclaimed productions of <em>The Killer Angels</em>, <em>The Return of the King</em>, and <em>The Two Towers</em>. Some other theatres around town that he has worked at include: Goodman, Court, Roadworks, Famous Door, National Jewish, Eclipse, Redtwist, Collaboraction, Stage Left, The Hypocrites, The Side Project, Thunder Road, About Face, and many others. </p>\n<p>John has been lucky enough to appear in many commercials, including a slew of national Nintendo spots for various sports games. He also does some voice-over work around town. Television credits include two episodes of <em>Prison Break</em>. Film credits include <em>Jack Slash</em> and <em>Nevel is the Devil</em>. </p>\n<p>John holds a BFA in Acting from The Theatre School at Depaul University and is proudly represented by Paonessa Talent. When not running around pretending to be other people John enjoys delving into worlds of sci-fi and fantasy through literature and, if he\'s lucky, getting to play Dungeons and Dragons with his awesome friends who have a campaign that\'s been running for roughly seven years now! He is an admitted geek. He wants to thank his amazing wife, Chelsea, for bringing him back from the dead and constantly reminding him how amazing life is.</p>',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(476,679,1,'Hero image paulfagen','2019-07-30 00:40:27','2019-08-04 03:39:28','68060942-32bc-4279-851a-d0ac164d4e3e',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(477,680,1,'Paul Fagen','2019-07-30 00:40:29','2019-07-30 00:40:29','dc709f87-1e2e-43b3-8662-e8dd5f2a1036',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Paul Fagen joined the Strawdog ensemble after his 2009 performance in <em>Red Noses.</em> Other Strawdog credits include <em>Quiz Show, Once in a Lifetime, The Good Soul of Szechuan, The Petrified Forest, Big Love,</em> and <em>The Duchess of Malfi.</em> Chicago credits include <em>Feathers and Teeth</em> (u/s Goodman Theatre), <em>Since, I Suppose</em>(Chicago Shakespeare Theatre), <em>The Metal Chidren</em> (Next Theatre), <em>The Language Archive</em> (Piven Theatre Workshop), <em>The Temperamentals</em> (About Face Theatre), <em>Company</em> and <em>The Burnt Part Boys</em> (Griffin Theatre), <em>The Attempters</em> and <em>The Nutrcracker</em>(The House Theatre of Chicago), <em>Bright Room Called Day</em> and <em>The Crucible</em> (Speaking Ring Theater) and multiple performances at Quest Theatre Ensemble. In 2008, Paul received a CAAP grant from the Chicago Department of Cultural Affairs which he used to study in New York under Ruth Maleczech, founder of the Mabou Mines company. Film credits include the indie short <em>Making the Bed</em> and Stephen Cone\'s soon to be released <em>Princess Cyd.</em> Television: <em>Chicago Fire</em> (NBC). Paul is represented by Big Mouth Talent. Learn more about Paul at <a href=\"http://www.paulfagenactor.com/\">www.paulfagenactor.com.</a><br /></p>',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(478,681,1,'Kamille Dawkins in Barbecue.','2019-07-30 00:40:52','2019-08-08 01:17:24','ebe3b654-2e52-491d-b701-7e3f536a4cd7',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(479,682,1,'Kamille Dawkins','2019-07-30 00:40:55','2019-07-30 00:40:55','d55ddd48-2630-45af-921c-960bad163b70',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Kamille Dawkins hails from the island of Jamaica and has been performing in Chicago since 2014. Following her first show, <em>If Scrooge Was A Brother</em> with ETA Creative Arts Foundation, she became a Black Theater Alliance nominee for the 2015 Phylicia Rashad Award for Most Promising Actress. Since then she has been featured as an actor, singer and musician in Filament\'s <em>Pinocchio,</em> The House Theatre\'s <em>The Revel</em> and Strawdog Theatre\'s <em>Once In a Lifetime</em> among other shows. In 2017 Kamille performed <em>Phillis: American Revolutionary</em> with Redd World Opera and <em>Gender Breakdown</em> with Collaboraction Theatre.</p>',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(480,683,1,'Scott Danielson in Improbable Frequency.','2019-07-30 00:41:20','2019-08-08 01:17:09','a827403e-f669-486e-a72d-255dbadd81bf',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(481,684,1,'Scott Danielson','2019-07-30 00:41:23','2019-07-30 00:41:23','15a1f218-853e-48f0-b8da-4be269b46b22',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Scott first appeared on Strawdog\'s stage in the 2013 production of <em>Improbable Frequency,</em> and is incredibly honored to call Strawdog his artistic home. An Illinois State University alumni, Scott has been living and performing in Chicago for about 10 years. Recent productions include <em>Quiz Show</em> (Strawdog), <em>The Full Monty</em> (Kokandy Productions, Jeff Nomination - Best Supporting Actor in a Musical), <em>Parade</em> (BoHo Theatre), and <em>The Arsonists</em>(Strawdog). He\'ll return to Strawdog\'s stage in 2016 playing George in <em>Once In A Lifetime.</em><br /><br />Scott has worked with a variety of theatres throughout the years, including Marriott Lincolnshire, Drury Lane, BoHo Theatre Company, Mary-Arrchie, Signal Ensemble, Awkward Pause, and many others. He is also an ensemble member of Octavarius, the Chicago born, L.A. based comedy/improv group, and is represented by Shirley Hamilton. Scott lives with his lovely wife and their two cuddly kittens, Sookie and Shakespeare. For more information, please visit <a href=\"http://www.scottdanielson.com/\">www.scottdanielson.com</a>.</p>',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(482,685,1,'Hero image michaeldailey','2019-07-30 00:41:47','2019-08-04 03:39:29','0cea098d-efe3-40d5-a1c7-85644f630f11',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(483,686,1,'Michael Dailey','2019-07-30 00:41:50','2019-07-30 00:41:50','2c8c0aa1-9a5f-4cfb-814c-5ca5eba68a58',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Michael has been a company member since 1997. He has appeared as an actor in 24 Strawdog productions, wrote scripts for Strawdog Radio Theatre 7 and was the script editor for <em>1001 Afternoons in Chicago, Measure for Measure</em> and <em>Julius Caesar.</em> On the administrative side he has served as Co-Artistic Director, Facilities Manager and Rental Agent. He has also worked as an actor for The Lyric Opera, Steppenwolf, About Face, Writers Theatre, St. Louis Shakespeare Festival, The Black Ensemble, Stage Left and Fox Valley Rep., among others. He is a graduate of Illinois State University, The Second City Training Center and is a Steppenwolf Acting Fellowship Recipient<br /></p>',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(484,687,1,'Lighting design by Claire Chrzan.','2019-07-30 00:42:17','2019-08-08 01:15:34','e99f51d4-945b-44f1-a6f3-468a9e45cc31',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(485,688,1,'Claire Chrzan','2019-07-30 00:42:19','2019-07-30 00:42:19','160f60d2-da60-4ddc-ab7e-0cad21f656ca',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Claire Chrzan grew up in the suburbs and has lived in Chicago for the last 10 years. For Strawdog she has designed <em>The Night Season</em> and <em>After Miss Julie,</em> and collaborations between Strawdog and the Forks and Hope Ensemble including <em>The Pied Piper</em> and <em>Best Beloved: The Just So Stories.</em><br /><br />As a full time freelance lighting designer Claire has also had the pleasure of designing with A Red Orchid, Haven, Manual Cinema, Chicago Children\'s Theatre, Sideshow, Jackalope, First Floor Theatre, About Face, The Gift, and more.<br /><br />Claire also works as a production stage manager for various dance companies affording her the opprotunity to travel nationally and internationally on tour.<br /><br />For more information please visit <a href=\"http://strawdog.org/clairechrzandesigns.com\">clairechrzandesigns.com</a></p>',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(486,689,1,'Set design by Hank Boland.','2019-07-30 00:42:44','2019-08-08 01:21:15','c7742563-1aa1-405a-988c-78808c7969a2',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(487,690,1,'Hank Boland','2019-07-30 00:42:46','2019-07-30 00:42:46','c8dd90ba-4b66-421a-9114-13a06cd40a96',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Hank\'s work with Strawdog includes Season Seventeen\'s epic musical <em>The True Ballad of Fall\'s Blessings,</em> written in collaboration with Strawdog Theatre Company, which premiered in 2005 and was directed by Nic Dimond. In Season Eighteen he contributed \"The Adventures of the Glenwood Springs Kid: The War Mask of El Dorado,\" Directed by Gregor Mortis, to Wireless Program Four. In Season Nineteen he was the author of <em>Strawdog Radio Theatre Six: A Many-Splendored Thing,</em> Directed by Jennifer Avery.<br /><br />In 2006, Nic Dimond asked Hank to developed and oversee the Strawdog Ensemble Writing Initiative, more modestly known as The Hit Factory! Several graduation services and evenings of The Hit Factory Presents are evidence that the Strawdog Ensemble Writing Initiative is not only committed to creating new works, but also committed to strengthening the working relationships between Strawdog and other members of the Chicago Theatre Community. <br /><br />In 2008 Hank was asked to join the Strawdog ensemble, and held the position of Managing Director from 2009-2011. He is currently Strawdog�s Director of New Works as well as the director of Strawdog�s popular late night offering THEATRE WARS! <br /><br />Hank was born in Green Bay, Wisconsin, raised in Pensacola, Florida, and has lived in Chicago since 1990. He attended Florida State University, Pensacola Junior College, has taken writing workshops at Second City, and has a Bachelor\'s Degree in Film from Columbia College in Chicago. He has been an adjunct faculty member in the Film Department of Columbia College Chicago since 2004 where he teaches a variety of screenwriting classes.<br /><br />His writings include numerous pieces at Strawdog, as well as co-authoring four musical comedies, a commissioned piece with 2nd Story, and most recently adapting a piece for BARREL OF MONKEYS. He holds an MFA in Playwriting through Spalding University in Louisville, Kentucky. He also serves on the Board of Directors for The League of Chicago Theaters.</p>',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(488,691,1,'Nicole Bloomsmith singing and playing guitar.','2019-07-30 00:43:07','2019-08-08 01:14:50','d519c313-8407-4897-8139-00744d9575e7',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NUL