OD 3: REQUISITION OF DOOM, THE LONG CHRISTMAS RIDE HOME, CYMBELINE, and DAMASCUS. He’s directed fights for many, many Strawdog productions, including GREAT EXPECTATIONS, BARBECUE, AFTER MISS JULIE, CHARLES IVES TAKE ME HOME, ROBIN HOOD, QUIZ SHOW, and more. </p>\n<p>Acting credits include THE BOOK OF WILL (Northlight Theatre), A LOSS OF ROSES and PLAYBOY OF THE WESTERN WORLD (Raven Theatre), THE DIARY OF ANNE FRANK (Writers Theatre), CYMBELINE and HAMLET (Michigan Shakespeare Festival), productions with The Factory, Oak Park Festival Theatre, and Jackalope, and understudy roles at Steppenwolf, Chicago Shakespeare Theatre, Writers, and Northlight.</p>\n<p>Fight direction credits include productions with Court Theatre, Northlight, Steppenwolf for Young Adults, Timeline, Victory Gardens, Raven, Steep, Jackalope, Teatro Vista, Redtwist, First Floor, The Artistic Home, Haven Theatre, and the late Mary-Arrchie.</p>\n<p>Sam is a graduate of Columbia College Chicago and represented by the fine folks at Grossman &amp; Jack and NV Talent.</p>',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(624,993,1,'Sam Hubbard','2019-07-30 04:14:27','2019-07-30 04:14:27','5ba56caf-012f-4fea-b3c9-b304a7050ce3',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Sam Hubbard has appeared in Strawdog’s <em>Neighborhood 3: Requisition of Doom, The Long Christmas Ride Home, Cymbeline, </em>and<em> Damascus. </em>He’s directed fights for many, many Strawdog productions, including <em>Great Expectations, Barbecue, After Miss Julie, Charles Ives Take Me Home, Robin Hood, Quiz Show, </em>and more. </p>\n<p>Acting credits include <em>The Book of Will</em> (Northlight Theatre), <em>A Loss of Roses</em> and <em>Playboy of the Western World</em> (Raven Theatre), <em>The Diary of Anne Frank</em> (Writers Theatre), <em>Cymbeline</em> and <em>Hamlet</em> (Michigan Shakespeare Festival), productions with The Factory, Oak Park Festival Theatre, and Jackalope, and understudy roles at Steppenwolf, Chicago Shakespeare Theatre, Writers, and Northlight.</p>\n<p>Fight direction credits include productions with Court Theatre, Northlight, Steppenwolf for Young Adults, Timeline, Victory Gardens, Raven, Steep, Jackalope, Teatro Vista, Redtwist, First Floor, The Artistic Home, Haven Theatre, and the late Mary-Arrchie.</p>\n<p>Sam is a graduate of Columbia College Chicago and represented by the fine folks at Grossman &amp; Jack and NV Talent.</p>',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(625,994,1,'Daniella Pereira','2019-07-30 04:18:33','2019-07-30 04:18:33','02ae6008-b4b4-425b-9dfe-da2f6738a453',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Originally from Miami, Florida, this little Latina left everything she knew to pursue her dreams in the frigid Windy City. She received a Bachelor in Fine Arts at the Chicago College of Performing Arts. Although she has still not become accustomed to the weather, even after being here for five years, she is truly in awe of the city and its magic. She is a proud first-generation Colombian American.</p>\n<p>Since graduating, Daniella has appeared in <em>Letters Home</em> (Griffin Theatre Company), <em>The Taming of the Shrew</em> (Oak Park Festival Theatre), <em>Here Lies the water/Here stands the man</em> (Nadja Leonard-Hopper and Genevieve Fowler), <em>Cymbeline</em> (Strawdog Theatre Company), and <em>Women Laughing Alone with Salad </em>(Theatre Wit).</p>\n<p>Daniella is honored and incredibly thankful to be joining Strawdog\'s ensemble, and cannot wait to work with such determined and inspiring individuals. She is represented by Gray Talent Group.</p>\n<p>Daniella loves the sun, the water, the sand between her toes, and pretty much everything that has to do with outer space.</p>',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(626,995,1,'Daniella Pereira','2019-07-30 04:18:54','2019-07-30 04:18:54','cd2b5516-3e24-412e-a9a5-025c79d54031',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Originally from Miami, Florida, this little Latina left everything she knew to pursue her dreams in the frigid Windy City. She received a Bachelor in Fine Arts at the Chicago College of Performing Arts. Although she has still not become accustomed to the weather, even after being here for five years, she is truly in awe of the city and its magic. She is a proud first-generation Colombian American.</p>\n<p>Since graduating, Daniella has appeared in <em>Letters Home</em> (Griffin Theatre Company), <em>The Taming of the Shrew</em> (Oak Park Festival Theatre), <em>Here Lies the water/Here stands the man</em> (Nadja Leonard-Hopper and Genevieve Fowler), <em>Cymbeline</em> (Strawdog Theatre Company), and <em>Women Laughing Alone with Salad </em>(Theatre Wit).</p>\n<p>Daniella is honored and incredibly thankful to be joining Strawdog\'s ensemble, and cannot wait to work with such determined and inspiring individuals. She is represented by Gray Talent Group.</p>\n<p>Daniella loves the sun, the water, the sand between her toes, and pretty much everything that has to do with outer space.</p>',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(627,996,1,'Leda Hoffmann','2019-07-30 04:19:40','2019-07-30 04:19:40','b68060a7-c775-4a53-83d3-53c00e72f19e',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Leda Hoffmann served on Milwaukee Rep’s Artistic Staff for seven years, working in the Education and Literary department before founding Milwaukee Rep’s Community Engagement Department. As the Director of Community Engagement, Leda envisioned and executed the Community Conversations program, enriching enriching audience experiences with robust small group dialogue; started Milwaukee Rep\'s Professional Training Institute; and developed long-term sustainable community programs through the Pillar Partner program.</p>\n<p>As the Artistic Director of Luminous Theatre, Leda produced and directed site-specific productions of <em>Mr. Burns: A Post-Electric Play</em> and <em>The Penelopiad.</em></p>\n<p>Since moving to Chicago, Leda has been directing and teaching with Mudlark Theater, Northbrook Park District, and Skyline Studios. Leda\'s work as a director has been seen across the Midwest at Milwaukee Rep (<em>A Christmas Carol, Black Pearl Sings!, Lady Day at Emerson\'s Bar and Grill, The Amish Project</em>), Illinois Shakespeare Festival (<em>Hamlet</em>), Door Shakespeare (<em>The Comedy of Errors, The Tempest, Romeo and </em><em>Juliet</em>), Milwaukee Chamber Theatre (<em>A Lovely Sunday for Creve Coeur</em>), Renaissance Theaterworks (<em>Censored on Final Approach</em>), The Alchemist Theatre (<em>The Chairs, King Lear</em>), Max and Louie Productions (<em>Lady Day at Emerson\'s Bar and Grill</em>), and Riverside Theater Iowa City (<em>Birth Witches</em>).</p>\n<p>Leda is a proud graduate of Grinnell College, a former Milwaukee Rep directing intern, former Harvard Stage apprentice, SDCF Observer, a member of Lincoln Center Theater Directors Lab, and an Artistic Associate with Kokandy Productions. Upcoming Chicago productions include <em>The Amish Project</em> at the Jedlicka Performing Arts Center and <em>Bobbins and Thread</em> at Mudlark Theater.</p>',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(628,997,1,'Leda Hoffmann','