Claire Chrzan','2019-07-30 04:34:33','2019-07-30 04:34:33','48459cfe-31e3-4733-8047-0001c8f95b95',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Claire Chrzan grew up in the suburbs and has lived in Chicago for the last 10 years. For Strawdog she has designed THE NIGHT SEASON and AFTER MISS JULIE, and collaborations between Strawdog and the Forks and Hope Ensemble, including THE PIED PIPER and BEST BELOVED: THE JUST SO STORIES.</p><p>As a full-time freelance lighting designer, Claire has also had the pleasure of designing with A Red Orchid, Haven, Manual Cinema, Chicago Children’s Theatre, Sideshow, Jackalope, First Floor Theatre, About Face, The Gift, and more.</p><p>Claire also works as a production stage manager for various dance companies, affording her the opportunity to travel nationally and internationally on tour.</p><p>For more information please visit <a href=\"http://clairechrzandesigns.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">clairechrzandesigns.com</a></p>',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(647,1016,1,'Michael Dailey','2019-07-30 04:35:12','2019-07-30 04:35:12','1926986d-e15f-4746-ba3c-ce4d65a20918',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Michael has been a company member since 1997. He has appeared as an actor in twenty-four Strawdog productions, wrote scripts for Strawdog Radio Theatre 7, and was the script editor for 1001 AFTERNOONS IN CHICAGO, MEASURE FOR MEASURE, and JULIUS CAESAR. On the administrative side, he has served as Co-Artistic Director, Facilities Manager, and Rental Agent.</p>\n<p>He has also worked as an actor for The Lyric Opera, Steppenwolf, About Face, Writers Theatre, St. Louis Shakespeare Festival, The Black Ensemble, Stage Left and Fox Valley Rep., among others. He is a graduate of Illinois State University and The Second City Training Center, and is a Steppenwolf Acting Fellowship Recipient.</p>',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(648,1017,1,'Michael Dailey','2019-07-30 04:35:20','2019-07-30 04:35:20','f94632d3-dcf6-4ac0-8e9a-da20f9752363',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Michael has been a company member since 1997. He has appeared as an actor in twenty-four Strawdog productions, wrote scripts for Strawdog Radio Theatre 7, and was the script editor for 1001 AFTERNOONS IN CHICAGO, MEASURE FOR MEASURE, and JULIUS CAESAR. On the administrative side, he has served as Co-Artistic Director, Facilities Manager, and Rental Agent.</p>\n<p>He has also worked as an actor for The Lyric Opera, Steppenwolf, About Face, Writers Theatre, St. Louis Shakespeare Festival, The Black Ensemble, Stage Left and Fox Valley Rep., among others. He is a graduate of Illinois State University and The Second City Training Center, and is a Steppenwolf Acting Fellowship Recipient.</p>',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(649,1018,1,'Scott Danielson','2019-07-30 04:36:14','2019-07-30 04:36:14','6ba533dd-4c9c-4358-9f5e-d2e7b2a09ac4',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Scott first appeared on Strawdog’s stage in the 2013 production of IMPROBABLE FREQUENCY, and is incredibly honored to call Strawdog his artistic home. An Illinois State University alumni, Scott has been living and performing in Chicago for about ten years. Recent productions include QUIZ SHOW (Strawdog), THE FULL MONTY (Kokandy Productions, Jeff Nomination, Best Supporting Actor in a Musical), PARADE (BoHo Theatre), and THE ARSONISTS (Strawdog). He returned to Strawdog’s stage in 2016 playing George in ONCE IN A LIFETIME.</p>\n<p>Scott has worked with a variety of theatres throughout the years, including Marriott Lincolnshire, Drury Lane, BoHo Theatre Company, Mary-Arrchie, Signal Ensemble, Awkward Pause, and many others. He is also an ensemble member of Octavarius, the Chicago born, L.A. based comedy/improv group, and is represented by Shirley Hamilton. </p>\n<p>Scott lives with his lovely wife and their two cuddly kittens, Sookie and Shakespeare. For more information, please visit <a href=\"http://www.scottdanielson.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">www.scottdanielson.com</a>.</p>',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(650,1019,1,'Kamille Dawkins','2019-07-30 04:36:46','2019-07-30 04:36:46','0d16ba7e-2e4b-4fc2-8a35-05206953865e',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Kamille Dawkins hails from the island of Jamaica and has been performing in Chicago since 2014. Following her first show, IF SCROOGE WAS A BROTHER with ETA Creative Arts Foundation, she became a Black Theater Alliance nominee for the 2015 Phylicia Rashad Award for Most Promising Actress. </p>\n<p>Since then she has been featured as an actor, singer, and musician in Filament’s PINOCCHIO, The House Theatre’s THE REVEL and Strawdog Theatre’s ONCE IN A LIFETIME, among other shows. In 2017 Kamille performed PHILLIS: AMERICAN REVOLUTIONARY with Redd World Opera and GENDER BREAKDOWN with Collaboraction Theatre.</p>',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(651,1020,1,'Sam Hubbard','2019-07-30 04:37:29','2019-07-30 04:37:29','cbbc7098-3295-4baa-83b2-2308a8f29722',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Sam Hubbard has appeared in Strawdog’s NEIGHBORHOOD 3: REQUISITION OF DOOM, THE LONG CHRISTMAS RIDE HOME, CYMBELINE, and DAMASCUS. He’s directed fights for many, many Strawdog productions, including GREAT EXPECTATIONS, BARBECUE, AFTER MISS JULIE, CHARLES IVES TAKE ME HOME, ROBIN HOOD, QUIZ SHOW, and more.</p>\n<p>Acting credits include THE BOOK OF WILL (Northlight Theatre), A LOSS OF ROSES and PLAYBOY OF THE WESTERN WORLD (Raven Theatre), THE DIARY OF ANNE FRANK (Writers Theatre), CYMBELINE and HAMLET (Michigan Shakespeare Festival), productions with The Factory, Oak Park Festival Theatre, and Jackalope, and understudy roles at Steppenwolf, Chicago Shakespeare Theatre, Writers, and Northlight.</p>\n<p>Fight direction credits include productions with Court Theatre, Northlight, Steppenwolf for Young Adults, Timeline, Victory Gardens, Raven, Steep, Jackalope, Teatro Vista, Redtwist, First Floor, The Artistic Home, Haven Theatre, and the late Mary-Arrchie.</p>\n<p>Sam is a graduate of Columbia College Chicago and represented by the fine folks at Grossman &amp; Jack and NV Talent.</p>',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(652,1021,1,'Barbecue','2019-07-30 04:41:07','2019-07-30 04:41:07','51589e9a-a76e-4041-b413-ec22b1ba0b68',NULL,NULL,'<p>By Robert O’Hara</p>\n<p>Directed by Damon Kiely</p>','','2017-08-17 07:00:00','2017-09-30 07:00:00',NULL,NULL,'<p>A modern American family uses a summer barbecue as a pretext to ambush sister Barbara with an intervention. If you think “all families are crazy” is just a cliché, you’ve not spent time under the influence of the O’Mallerys. An afternoon in the park with these raucous siblings, and you’ll be challenging your own assumptions about family, race, and reality. The Chicago premiere of <em>Barbecue</em> by Obie and Helen Hayes Award winner Robert O’Hara will have you laughing out loud and questioning how it’s true that 