 when time is of the essence you want your muscles to respond efficiently.</p><p><strong>Practicing Assertiveness Skills &amp; Setting Boundaries:</strong>Early in the class, a Licensed Clinical Professional Counselor introduces effective communication styles and the importance of assertiveness techniques. Acknowledging womxn face threats from intimate partners and acquaintances, this discussion emphasizes: boundary setting, self-respect and the monitoring of relationship dynamics.</p><p><strong>Providing Support:</strong> We acknowledge and welcome the potential presence of survivors in the room and recognize that aspects of the workshop may be challenging and sensitive by nature. Support is provided throughout the workshop to anyone, as needed, by a Licensed Clinical Professional Counselor.</p><p>This course requires no martial arts training, nor extreme physical aptitudes. All skill levels are welcome and encouraged. </p><p><a href=\"https://www.chicagomindandbody.com/about-the-founder/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><strong>Sarah Farris</strong></a> (she/her/hers) works as a therapist and part-time nutrition counselor. She curates healthy lifestyle practices for her clients. She has also expanded a new business \"Chicago Mind &amp; Body\"</p><p><strong>Cassidy Hill</strong> (she/her/hers) As a Certified Personal Trainer with an affinity for martial arts, Cassidy Hill loves helping people feel strong, confident, and capable. Her self defense background involves a hefty combination of Tae Kwon Do, Kung Fu, Hapkido, and Aikido. She is thrilled to be working with By Womxn For Womxn, which offers both a safe space, and a unique environment where we get to lift each other up, showing each other how powerful we can truly be. </p><p><a href=\"http://strawdog.org/index.php?shot=mpetro_large.jpg&amp;section=company&amp;person=michaelapetro\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><strong>Michaela Petro</strong></a> (she/her/hers) is an actor and certified trainer of self-defense &amp; rape prevention with the American Women\'s Self-Defense Association (AWSDA). As an ensemble member of Strawdog Theatre Company, one of her core beliefs is serving her community and does so by sharing empowerment skills.</p>','$40','https://red.vendini.com/ticket-software.html?t=tix&e=22a03b7c38d433a51f2ac69c3fd10a2a','<p>A new way, led by womxn: learn a three-tiered approach to self-defense for all skill levels.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(771,1501,1,'For Womxn, By Womxn','2019-08-01 01:20:00','2019-08-01 01:20:00','b9e878ce-d760-4b96-9862-17c02400ba1f',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Curated by Michaela Petro, an instructor certified in rape prevention and self-defense, with certified personal trainer Cassidy Hill, and licensed clinical professional counselor Sarah Farris, to offer a 3-tiered approach to self-defense focused on recognition of predators &amp; escaping dangerous situations.</p>\n<p><strong>A New Way, Led by Womxn:</strong> The basic self-defense training womxn receive is often inadequate and outdated. FW, BW is looking to change what, and how, we teach each other to ensure no measure of confidence is overlooked or untapped. It is our responsibility to arm ourselves with information, physical preparation and self-defense strategies to protect our basic human right to live. We recognize that too many womxn experience threats to their safety at some point in their lives, and predatory attacks transcend age, gender, race &amp; culture.</p>\n<p><strong>Incorporating Strength-Training:</strong> Learning the fundamentals of self-defense is important, and being physically able to complete the movements is paramount. Strength-training not only improves your body’s ability to move about in the world, it improves one’s mind-body connection which directly sharpens one’s awareness and intuition throughout the day. Stronger bodies mean faster reflexes, and when time is of the essence you want your muscles to respond efficiently.</p>\n<p><strong>Practicing Assertiveness Skills &amp; Setting Boundaries:</strong>Early in the class, a Licensed Clinical Professional Counselor introduces effective communication styles and the importance of assertiveness techniques. Acknowledging womxn face threats from intimate partners and acquaintances, this discussion emphasizes: boundary setting, self-respect and the monitoring of relationship dynamics.</p>\n<p><strong>Providing Support:</strong> We acknowledge and welcome the potential presence of survivors in the room and recognize that aspects of the workshop may be challenging and sensitive by nature. Support is provided throughout the workshop to anyone, as needed, by a Licensed Clinical Professional Counselor.</p>\n<p>This course requires no martial arts training, nor extreme physical aptitudes. All skill levels are welcome and encouraged. </p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.chicagomindandbody.com/about-the-founder/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><strong>Sarah Farris</strong></a> (she/her/hers) works as a therapist and part-time nutrition counselor. She curates healthy lifestyle practices for her clients. She has also expanded a new business \"Chicago Mind &amp; Body\"</p>\n<p><strong>Cassidy Hill</strong> (she/her/hers) As a Certified Personal Trainer with an affinity for martial arts, Cassidy Hill loves helping people feel strong, confident, and capable. Her self defense background involves a hefty combination of Tae Kwon Do, Kung Fu, Hapkido, and Aikido. She is thrilled to be working with By Womxn For Womxn, which offers both a safe space, and a unique environment where we get to lift each other up, showing each other how powerful we can truly be. </p>\n<p><a href=\"http://strawdog.org/index.php?shot=mpetro_large.jpg&amp;section=company&amp;person=michaelapetro\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><strong>Michaela Petro</strong></a> (she/her/hers) is an actor and certified trainer of self-defense &amp; rape prevention with the American Women\'s Self-Defense Association (AWSDA). As an ensemble member of Strawdog Theatre Company, one of her core beliefs is serving her community and does so by sharing empowerment skills.</p>','$40','https://red.vendini.com/ticket-software.html?t=tix&e=22a03b7c38d433a51f2ac69c3fd10a2a','<p>A new way, led by womxn: learn a three-tiered approach to self-defense for all skill levels.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(772,1504,1,'Company','2019-08-01 01:20:20','2019-08-01 01:20:20','816d3a3e-bb04-45ec-a92b-c0b45c548b41',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>The whole wide world in a little black box.</p>\n<p>Strawdog Theatre Company is committed to ensemble acting and an immersive design approach, offering Chicago the premiere storefront theatre experience. We develop new work, re-imagine classic plays, explore new fusions of music and theatre, ask provocative questions and deliver the unexpected to our audience.</p><p>We provide a home for our celebrated ensemble to work and play with the most sought after artists in Chicago theatre along with the best new talents in the city.</p>\n<p>Founded in 1988.</p>','<p>Mike Aden<br /></p>\n<p>Jennifer H. Banys</p>\n<p>Meaghan Clayton</p>\n<p>Camille McLeod</p>\n<p>Jennifer Nelson</p>\n<p>Seth Rickard</p>\n<p>Jeff Ziemer</p>','<p>MANAGING DIRECTOR<br />Leah Barish<br /></p>\n<p>CO-ARTISTIC DIRECTOR<br />Michael Dailey<br /></p>\n<p>CO-ARTISTIC DIRECTOR<br />Heath Hays</p>\n<p>LITERARY MANAGER<br />Cara Beth Heath</p>\n<p>CASTING DIRECTOR<br />Kanomé Jones</p>\n<p>CO-ARTISTIC DIRECTOR<br />Anderson Lawfer</p>\n<p>PRODUCTION MANAGER<br />Becca Levy